    dc:creator "Crews, Sarah C." ;
    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "Two new species of flattie spiders (Araneae: Selenopidae) and descriptions of undescribed males from the Caribbean" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1437456> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1437456>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–12. Selenops petrunkevitchi Alayón male paratype from Blue Mountains Peak, Jamaica (USNM 00003309A). 1 habitus; 2–3 male pedipalp (2 ventral, 3 retrolateral). Selenops pensilis Muma male from Villa Elisa, Dominican Republic (USNM 00784714). 4 habitus; 5–6 male pedipalp (5 ventral, 6 retrolateral). Selenops anacaona sp. nov. female holotype from Parque Jaragua, Dominican Republic (AMNH). 7 habitus; 8 epigyne; 9 vulva. Selenops caonabo sp. nov. female holotype from Los Tablones, Dominican Republic (USNM 00782859). 10 habitus; 11 epigyne; 12 vulva. Scale bar = 5 mm (1, 4, 7, 10), 1 mm (2, 3, 5, 6), 0.5 mm (8, 9, 11, 12)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1437456/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

